                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Quincy Ill. Sept. 11. 1890<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. Dr S. Morais<lb/>
                Philadelphia Pa<lb/>
                Rev. dear Sir and Friend&#59;<lb/></p>
            <p>My departure from Ph<hi rend="sup">a</hi> was so sudden<lb/> and unexpected&#44; that no time was left me to bid<lb/> farewell to my Colleagues and friends I leave behind.<lb/>  The dispatch calling me hither reached me on Tuesday<lb/> and on the noon of the following day I left.  I beg of you<lb/> to accept this as an excuse for my seemingly rude<lb/> neglect.  I have accepted the position as Rabbi<lb/> of the Bnai Sholen Cngr. for the term of three years at a<lb/> salary sufficient to satisfy my wants.<lb/></p>
            <p>My experiences during my seven years stay in Ph<hi rend="sup">a</hi><lb/> were not free of cares&#44; troubles and struggles&#44; but I regret<lb/> them not.  They have brought me in contact with good and<lb/> noble men&#44; by whose example I could not but profit.<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>In looking back over these last years I feel delight in<lb/> and am highly gratified&#44; for they have favored me in<lb/> forming your <sic>aquaintance</sic> and let me hope in gaining<lb/> your friendship.  Please remember me in kindness.<lb/></p>  
            <p>May God protect you and yours from all harm.  Wishing<lb/> you a &#91;Hebrew&#93;<lb/> I am Sincerely Yours<lb/> E Eppstein<lb/></p>
            <p>P. S. Please convey to Dr Spivak my regrets for not being<lb/> able to further serve in the Con. of fifteen of the<lb/> Jewish Alliance of Am. to which he kindly had<lb/> appointed me.<lb/></p>
                
            <p><sic>Adress</sic>&#58;<lb/>
                Rabbi E. Eppstein<lb/>
                Quincy Ill.<lb/></p>
            <p>General Delivery.<lb/></p>
            </body>
